cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use PRISM in your research or work, please cite it as below."
title: "PRISM: A Framework for LLM Research and Audits"
abstract: >-
  PRISM is a methodology for keeping multi-prompt, multi-session LLM research
  and audit work coherent across prompts, sessions, and the context limits of
  any single chat. It splits a research problem into atomic specialist prompts,
  runs each where it works best across Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini, and Perplexity,
  and converges their outputs into a single living document called the Starter.
  The framework codifies Monitors, Gates, Standing Principles, a two-layer
  convergence model, and version management — all distributed as a single
  markdown file that can be attached to any LLM session or installed as a
  Claude Skill.
